# Logo Component Rules

## Overview
Rules and patterns for the Logo component (`src/components/atoms/Logo.tsx`)

## Purpose
Brand logo with optional navigation capability

## Rules

### Core Requirements
- ✅ **Default Props:** Always provide sensible defaults (`href = "/"`)
- ✅ **TypeScript:** Use explicit prop types (`LogoProps`) with optional properties
- ✅ **Styling:** Use consistent brand colors (`text-[#8a0028]`) and typography (`text-xl font-semibold tracking-wide`)
- ✅ **Accessibility:** Logo should be wrapped in a Link for navigation
- ✅ **Export Pattern:** Export both named export and default export
- ✅ **Icon/Symbol:** Use star symbol (★) as brand identifier
- ✅ **Layout:** Use flexbox with gap for internal spacing

## Code Template
```typescript
import Link from "next/link";

type LogoProps = { href?: string };

export function Logo({ href = "/" }: LogoProps) {
  return (
    <Link href={href} className="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#8a0028]">
      <span className="text-xl font-semibold tracking-wide">★ PRET ★</span>
    </Link>
  );
}

export default Logo;
```

## Implementation Details

### Props
- `href` (optional): Navigation destination, defaults to "/"
- Type: `string | undefined`

### Styling Classes
- Container: `flex items-center gap-2 text-[#8a0028]`
- Text: `text-xl font-semibold tracking-wide`

### Brand Elements
- Primary brand color: `#8a0028`
- Brand symbol: ★ (star)
- Brand name: "PRET"
- Typography: Extra large, semi-bold, wide tracking

## Quality Checklist
- ✅ Logo text is visible and properly styled
- ✅ Default navigation works (href="/")
- ✅ Custom navigation works (when href prop provided)
- ✅ Brand colors are consistent
- ✅ Typography follows design system
- ✅ Component is properly exported